dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from an email from UNOCHA. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field 2. 5 blank Admin2 p-codes were populated by matching the value to the Admin2 name. 3. Found and fixed 7 multipart slivers 4. Admin0 p-code field now uses 2-letter ISO code 5. Admin3 unit "Gape Kpodji" has Admin2 Name attribution for "Zio" but its Admin3 p-code had Admin2 p-code portion for "Lacs". It has been given Admin2 p-code portion "TG0308" 6. Found and fixed 68 gap errors and 57 overlap errors
The following was found by ITOS but is not addressed in this version: 1. The slashes in some names suggest the presence of alternate names that should be separated and placed in an AltName field
